saRg.name: saRg

revisions.description: Initial release of reduced-set module for releases based on BFC 5.7.x.

saRg.description: Controls the behavior of router/wireless functions. Can be part of CM configuration file.

saRgDeviceMode.name: saRgDeviceMode
saRgDeviceMode.description: Defines the mode of operation for the device. This parameter is stored in non-vol and is multiSsid(1) by default. Setting this object via SNMP will cause the unit to reboot. This MIB will be superseded in the config file by TLV202. This MIB will read the proper value if set from TLV202. This MIB will be superseded by saRgIpMgmtLanMode inbridge(1) or mixed(4). disable(0): Value will reflect when TLV202 is set to 0. Not all platforms have this value implemented. multiSsid(1): Default Value. Value supports IPv4RG with multiple SSID configuration and bridge mode via saRgIpMgmtLanMode MIB. Bridge mode is the same as eRouter disabled mode. IPV4RG is the non eRouter behavior that existed before in our router products. Ipv4(3): eRouter IPv4 only mode Ipv6(4): eRouter IPv6 only mode Dualstack(5): eRouter IPv4 and IPv6 dualstack Note: cableHome11(2) support is not available.

saRgDeviceResetDefaultEnable.name: saRgDeviceResetDefaultEnable
saRgDeviceResetDefaultEnable.description: This object controls the reset to factory default functionality of the gateway. This prevents the local user from using the reset switch to gain access to the setup pages using the default user name and password. The objective is to prevent theft of service from a user who reconfigures the device to add users or change wireless settings. Enable (object set to true): 1. Momentary press of the Reset Switch (<5 seconds) DOCSIS restart of the modem (reboot, no reset to factory default values). 2. Pressing the reset switch for >5 seconds Reboots and resets of all values (modem and router) to factory default. Disable (object set to false): 1. Momentary press of the Reset Switch (<5 seconds) DOCSIS restart of the modem (reboot, no reset to factory default values). 2. Pressing the reset switch for >5 seconds Modem reboots and resets only the cable modem settings to factory default values. The router settings should remain and should not NOT reset to factory default.

saRgDeviceRemoteWebAccessPort.name: saRgDeviceRemoteWebAccessPort
saRgDeviceRemoteWebAccessPort.description: Defines what port to use for the WAN IP address of the gateway to be able to access RG web pages. This value is to be stored in non-vol and will persist across reboots. Only a factory reset would clear it

saRgDeviceLanLanIsolation.name: saRgDeviceLanLanIsolation
saRgDeviceLanLanIsolation.description: This MIB is only available in D3.0 products. This MIB does not take effect if the modem is in VLAN mode i.e if saRgIpMgmtLanMode.32=vlan(5). Lan-Lan Isolation allows you block IP access between CPEs connected to the Ethernet ports. Use this mib in conjunction with saRgDeviceLanWlanIsolation and saRgDot11BssApIsolation.x for complete isolation between CPEs connected to the RG. This MIB is written to non-vol and set to disable(0) after a factory reset. disable(0)- No Isolation enable(1)- Enable Isolation feature

saRgDeviceLanWlanIsolation.name: saRgDeviceLanWlanIsolation
saRgDeviceLanWlanIsolation.description: This MIB is only available in D3.0 products. This MIB does not take effect if the modem is in VLAN mode i.e if saRgIpMgmtLanMode.32=vlan(5). Lan-Wlan Isolation allows you block IP access between CPEs connected to the Ethernet port and Wireless SSIDs. Use this mib in conjunction with saRgDeviceLanLanIsolation and saRgDot11BssApIsolation.x for complete isolation between CPEs connected to the RG. This MIB is written to non-vol and set to disable(0) after a factory reset. disable(0)- No Isolation enable(1)- Enable Isolation feature

saRgDeviceIpv6Trans.name: saRgDeviceIpv6Trans
saRgDeviceIpv6Trans.description: This MIB will control which IPv6 transition technology is enabled on the device. After setting this MIB to disable in the config file, IPv4 traffic will pass normally through the device. When switched to dslite, the DSLite feature will be enabled. If eRouter is in IPv6-only mode, DS Lite will tunnel IPv4 traffic over IPv6 to the AFTR address specified either manually or in the DHCPv6 option-64. See saRgDslite MIB tree for more details. If this setting is changed by the config file, the CM will reboot. This MIB is written to non-vol and set to disable(0) after a factory reset. disable(0) - No technology is enabled enable(1) - DS lite feature is enabled

saRgDeviceIpv6Passthrough.name: saRgDeviceIpv6Passthrough
saRgDeviceIpv6Passthrough.description: This MIB controls IPv6 passthrough on the RG and is applicable in bridge and router modes. When disabled the RG will function without any IPv6 passthrough When IPv6 passthrough is enabled in Bridge Mode the RG will drop all IPv4 traffic When IPv6 passthrough is enabled in router mode the RG will operate as normal for IPv4 traffic, but all IPv6 traffic will passthrough This MIB requires CM reboot. This MIB is written to non-vol and set to disable(0) after a factory reset.

saRgDeviceFactoryReset.name: saRgDeviceFactoryReset
saRgDeviceFactoryReset.description: Set routerAndWifi(1) to restore default settings of both the router and wifi. Set routerOnly(2) to restore default settings of the router. Set wifi(3) to restore default settings of the wifi. Return false(0) when read.

saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpEnabled.name: saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpEnabled
saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpEnabled.description: Stored in non-vol, disabled after factory reset.

saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpServerTable.name: saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpServerTable
saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpServerTable.description: Up to 3 NTP servers are supported. This table is stored in non-vol. Default entries after factory reset are: 1: time.nist.gov 2: nist.aol-ca.truetime.com 3: nist1-ny.glassey.com

saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpServerAddress.name: saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpServerAddress
saRgDeviceTimeSetupNtpServerAddress.description: IP address or FQDN of the NTP server.

saRgDeviceTimeSetupZone.name: saRgDeviceTimeSetupZone
saRgDeviceTimeSetupZone.description: Time zone for the gateway. Stored in non-vol, gmtZeroDublinEdinburghLisbonLondon(26) after factory reset.

saRgDeviceTimeSetupDst.name: saRgDeviceTimeSetupDst
saRgDeviceTimeSetupDst.description: Daylight saving time. If set to 0, DST is disabled Stored in non-vol, 0 after factory reset.

saRgDeviceIanaIAID.name: saRgDeviceIanaIAID
saRgDeviceIanaIAID.description: Returns the IAID value embedded in the IA_NA for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIanaT1.name: saRgDeviceIanaT1
saRgDeviceIanaT1.description: Returns the T1 value embedded in the IA_NA for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIanaT2.name: saRgDeviceIanaT2
saRgDeviceIanaT2.description: Returns the T2 value embedded in the IA_NA for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIanaTable.name: saRgDeviceIanaTable
saRgDeviceIanaTable.description: Table of IA Address entries associated with IA_NA for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIanaEntry.name: saRgDeviceIanaEntry
saRgDeviceIanaEntry.description: Table of IA Address entries associated with IA_NA for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIanaValue.name: saRgDeviceIanaValue
saRgDeviceIanaValue.description: IPv6 address provided to the eRouter WAN interface via DHCPv6.

saRgDeviceIanaPreferredLifetime.name: saRgDeviceIanaPreferredLifetime
saRgDeviceIanaPreferredLifetime.description: Preferred Lifetime setting for an IPv6 address assigned to the eRouter.

saRgDeviceIanaValidLifetime.name: saRgDeviceIanaValidLifetime
saRgDeviceIanaValidLifetime.description: Valid Lifetime setting for an IPv6 address assigned to the eRouter.

saRgDeviceIapdIAID.name: saRgDeviceIapdIAID
saRgDeviceIapdIAID.description: Returns the IAID value embedded in the IA_PD for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIapdT1.name: saRgDeviceIapdT1
saRgDeviceIapdT1.description: Returns the T1 value embedded in the IA_PD for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIapdT2.name: saRgDeviceIapdT2
saRgDeviceIapdT2.description: Returns the T2 value embedded in the IA_PD for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIapdTable.name: saRgDeviceIapdTable
saRgDeviceIapdTable.description: Table of IA Prefix entries associated with IA_PD for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIapdEntry.name: saRgDeviceIapdEntry
saRgDeviceIapdEntry.description: Table of IA Address entries associated with IA_PD for the eRouter's DHCPv6 lease.

saRgDeviceIapdPreferredLifetime.name: saRgDeviceIapdPreferredLifetime
saRgDeviceIapdPreferredLifetime.description: Preferred Lifetime setting for an IPv6 address assigned to the eRouter.

saRgDeviceIapdValidLifetime.name: saRgDeviceIapdValidLifetime
saRgDeviceIapdValidLifetime.description: Valid Lifetime setting for an IPv6 address assigned to the eRouter.

saRgDeviceIapdPrefixValue.name: saRgDeviceIapdPrefixValue
saRgDeviceIapdPrefixValue.description: Prefix address specified in the IA_PD.

saRgDot11OnOffPushButtonTime.name: saRgDot11OnOffPushButtonTime
saRgDot11OnOffPushButtonTime.description: Specifies how long to press WPS button to enable or disable the WiFi interface (primary SSID). When set to 11, the feature is disabled. Stored in non-vol, 11 after factory reset.

saRgDot11BssEntry.name: saRgDot11BssEntry
saRgDot11BssEntry.description: A row in the table which represents parameters for SSID.

saRgDot11BssEnable.name: saRgDot11BssEnable
saRgDot11BssEnable.description: Controls the BSS state. When set to enableOnline(3), the SSID is enabled only when the cable modem is online. When the modem changes state to offline, the AP will send dissasociation messages to the STAs connected to the SSID and then disable. The value of primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is enabled(1) after factory reset. The other BSSs are disabled by default. If other BSS's SSID name is not defined, the BSS will not be enabled.

saRgDot11BssSsid.name: saRgDot11BssSsid
saRgDot11BssSsid.description: Controls and reflects the service set identifier. The value of primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset. If other BSS's SSID name is not defined, the BSS will not be enabled.

saRgDot11BssSecurityMode.name: saRgDot11BssSecurityMode
saRgDot11BssSecurityMode.description: Secrity for BSS. Beacause WPA2 is backwords compatible with WPA, setting this object to wpaWpa2Psk(7) is allowed and has the same effect as setting to wpa2Psk(3). The same is true for wpaWpa2Enterprise(8) and wpa2Enterprise(5). The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is wpaWpa2Psk(7) after factory reset. For each other BSS security has to be included in configuration file or the BSS will be disabled.

saRgDot11BssClosedNetwork.name: saRgDot11BssClosedNetwork
saRgDot11BssClosedNetwork.description: Controls whether the device will operate in closed network mode. If set to true(1), then the network mode is closed and the SSID will not be broadcast in beacon packets. If set to false(2), then the network mode is open and the SSID will be broadcast in beacon packets. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol. The default value for other BSSs is false.

saRgDot11BssAccessMode.name: saRgDot11BssAccessMode
saRgDot11BssAccessMode.description: Controls what stations will be given access to the device. If set to allowAny(0), then any station will be allowed to connect. If set to allowList(1), then only stations whose MAC address appears in the saRgDot11AccessMacTable will be allowed to connect. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol. The default value for other BSSs is 0.

saRgDot11BssMaxNumSta.name: saRgDot11BssMaxNumSta
saRgDot11BssMaxNumSta.description: This object defines the maximum number of STAs that can connect to this SSID. Note that the maximum number of STA accross all SSIDs in the AP is 128. Default value is 128 for all SSIDs. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol.

saRgDot11BssUserStatus.name: saRgDot11BssUserStatus
saRgDot11BssUserStatus.description: Provides the BSS Id Web UI or Wireless ON/OFF (if exist) status that is set by the user. If the user can press the Wireless ON/OFF (if exist) button and its status can be seen in BSS ID Web UI. If user changes access point status in Web UI, it will reflect the status of Wireless ON/OFF LED.

saRgDot11BssApIsolation.name: saRgDot11BssApIsolation
saRgDot11BssApIsolation.description: This MIB is only available in D3.0 products. AP Isolation (Access Point Isolation) allows you to isloate traffic between CPEs on the same Wifi SSID. This allows a measure of security to prevent hackers from accessing other CPEs in a public Wifi environment. Ex. When this MIB is enabled you can not ping between CPEs connected to the same SSID. AP Isolation is settable per SSID in either VLAN or non VLAN modes. This MIB is written to non-vol and set to disable(0) after a factory reset. disable(0)- No AP Isolation enable(1)- Enable AP Isolation feature.

saRgDot11BssSecSsidTrafficPriority.name: saRgDot11BssSecSsidTrafficPriority
saRgDot11BssSecSsidTrafficPriority.description: This MIB is only available in D3.0 products and applicable for secondary SSID in hotspot environment. When disabled, all the traffic to the secondary SSID in question would have same WMM QoS parameters as the primary SSID. When set to ac_bk(1), the secondary SSID traffic would be classified as AC_BK resulting in better DS prioritization for primary SSID traffic

saRgDot11BssRejectPriSsidSta.name: saRgDot11BssRejectPriSsidSta
saRgDot11BssRejectPriSsidSta.description: This MIB is only available in D3.0 products and applicable for secondary SSID in hotspot environment. By default, a private SSID STA can associate to hotspot SSID. This MIB can be used to reject private SSID STAs to associate with hotspot SSID if and only if STA has associated with private SSID once before.

saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidType.name: saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidType
saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidType.description: This object specifies the type of SSID used. mac6char(1): If saRgDot11BssSsid.32 is empty, the SSID is the last 3 bytes of DOCSIS MAC address, displayed as 6 lowercase hex characters. If saRgDot11BssSsid.32 is not empty, SSID is the value from saRgDot11BssSsid.32 (set by SNMP or the user). mac6char-prefix(2): the same as mac6char(2) with the prefix addition defined in saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidPrefix. If saRgDot11BssSsid.32 is not empty, this prefix does not show. mac4char-prefix(3): the same as mac6char-prefix(2) but 4 MAC characters instead of 6. prefix-force(4): The prefix is always included, even if saRgDot11BssSsid.32 is empty. Note: stored in non-vol. mac6char(1) after factory reset

saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidPrefix.name: saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidPrefix
saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidPrefix.description: The prefix for primary SSID, if saRgDot11BssSsid.32 is empty and saRgDot11BssPrimarySsidType is set to mac6char-prefix(2). Stored in non-vol. Empty after factory reset.

saRgDot11WpaEntry.name: saRgDot11WpaEntry
saRgDot11WpaEntry.description: A row in the table which represents WPA parameters for BSS.

saRgDot11WpaAlgorithm.name: saRgDot11WpaAlgorithm
saRgDot11WpaAlgorithm.description: The value of tkip(0) is not allowed when security is WPA2. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and tkipPlusAes(2) after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is tkip.

saRgDot11WpaPreSharedKey.name: saRgDot11WpaPreSharedKey
saRgDot11WpaPreSharedKey.description: Sets the WPA Pre-Shared Key (PSK). This value MUST be either a 64-digit hexadecimal number, OR a 8 to 63 character ASCII string. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is the serial number of the device after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is 8 0's. This object return an empty string when read.

saRgDot11WpaGroupRekeyInterval.name: saRgDot11WpaGroupRekeyInterval
saRgDot11WpaGroupRekeyInterval.description: Sets the WPA Group Rekey Interval in seconds. Set to zero to disable periodic rekeying. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is 3600 after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is 3600.

saRgDot11RadiusEntry.name: saRgDot11RadiusEntry
saRgDot11RadiusEntry.description: A row in the table which represents WPA parameters for BSS.

saRgDot11RadiusAddressType.name: saRgDot11RadiusAddressType
saRgDot11RadiusAddressType.description: Type of RADIUS server IP address.

saRgDot11RadiusAddress.name: saRgDot11RadiusAddress
saRgDot11RadiusAddress.description: Sets RADIUS server IP address. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is 0.0.0.0 after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is 0.0.0.0.

saRgDot11RadiusPort.name: saRgDot11RadiusPort
saRgDot11RadiusPort.description: Sets the UDP port used to communicate with the RADIUS server. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is 1645 after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is 1645.

saRgDot11RadiusKey.name: saRgDot11RadiusKey
saRgDot11RadiusKey.description: Sets or displays the RADIUS key. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is null after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is null. This object return an empty string when read.

saRgDot11RadiusReAuthInterval.name: saRgDot11RadiusReAuthInterval
saRgDot11RadiusReAuthInterval.description: Sets the RADIUS Rekey Interval in seconds. Set to zero to disable periodic rekeying. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is 3600 after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is 3600.

saRgDot11WepEntry.name: saRgDot11WepEntry
saRgDot11WepEntry.description: A row in the table which represents WPA parameters for BSS.

saRgDot11WepDefaultKey.name: saRgDot11WepDefaultKey
saRgDot11WepDefaultKey.description: Controls and reflects the default key which will be used when 64 or 128 bit encryption is enabled. Indicates the entry from the saRgDot1164BitKeyTable if saRgDot11EncryptionMode is set to wep64(1), or the entry from the saRgDot11128BitKeyTable if saRgDot11EncryptionMode is set to wep128(2). The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is 1 after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is 1.

saRgDot11WepEncryptionMode.name: saRgDot11WepEncryptionMode
saRgDot11WepEncryptionMode.description: The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is wep128(1) after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is wep128.

saRgDot11WepPassPhrase.name: saRgDot11WepPassPhrase
saRgDot11WepPassPhrase.description: Controls and reflects the WEP pass phrase. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is null after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is null. This object return an empty string when read.

saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyTable.name: saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyTable
saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyTable.description: A table of 40 bit key values used when saRgDot11WepEncryptionMode is set to wep64(0).

saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyEntry.name: saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyEntry
saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyEntry.description: A row in the table which represents a single 64 bit key.

saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyIndex.name: saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyIndex
saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyIndex.description: Identifies the instance of this table row.

saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyValue.name: saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyValue
saRgDot11Wep64BitKeyValue.description: A 40 bit key to be used when saRgDot11WepEncryptionMode is set to wep64(1). The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is all 1's after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is all 0's. This object return an empty string when read.

saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyTable.name: saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyTable
saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyTable.description: A table of 104 bit key values used when saRgDot11WepEncryptionMode is set to wep128(1).

saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyEntry.name: saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyEntry
saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyEntry.description: A row in the table which represents a single 128 bit key.

saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyIndex.name: saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyIndex
saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyIndex.description: Identifies the instance of this table row.

saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyValue.name: saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyValue
saRgDot11Wep128BitKeyValue.description: A 104 bit key to be used when saRgDot11WepEncryptionMode is set to wep128(2). The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is all 1's. The default value for other BSSs is all 0's. This object return an empty string when read.

saRgDot11PrivacyWpsPushButtonTime.name: saRgDot11PrivacyWpsPushButtonTime
saRgDot11PrivacyWpsPushButtonTime.description: Specifies how long to press WPS button to start the WPS procedure. 0 means disable WPS. Stored in non-vol, 1 after factory reset.

saRgDot11ClientTable.name: saRgDot11ClientTable
saRgDot11ClientTable.description: A table of wireless clients that are associated with the BSS.

saRgDot11ClientEntry.name: saRgDot11ClientEntry
saRgDot11ClientEntry.description: A row in the table that specifies a single station MAC address.

saRgDot11ClientIndex.name: saRgDot11ClientIndex
saRgDot11ClientIndex.description: Indicates the instance of this table row.

saRgDot11ClientStation.name: saRgDot11ClientStation
saRgDot11ClientStation.description: A MAC address of a client associated with the BSS.

saRgDot11ExtMgmtEntry.name: saRgDot11ExtMgmtEntry
saRgDot11ExtMgmtEntry.description: A row in the table which represents parameters for a Radio. Index 32 should be set for Radio 0 -- 2.4 GHz if populated. Index 112 should be set for Radio 1

saRgDot11ExtMbssUserControl.name: saRgDot11ExtMbssUserControl
saRgDot11ExtMbssUserControl.description: Sets the number of user controlled Wifi networks via web pages. 1: The user has control over the primary wireless network only. No guest network page is displayed. 2: The user has control over the primary wireless network and one guest network. No drop down menu (or only 1 item in the menu) for additional guest network configuration. 3: Same as above with 2 guest networks. 4: Same as above with 3 guest networks. 5: Same as above with 4 guest networks. 6: Same as above with 5 guest networks. 7: Same as above with 6 guest networks. 8: Same as above with 7 guest networks. Bit Mask Control: Bit 16: -- User has control over Primary Wireless Network : 65536 Bit 17: -- User has control over Guest Network 1 (interface 33) : 131072 Bit 18: -- User has control over Guest Network 2 (interface 34) : 262144 Bit 19: -- User has control over Guest Network 3 (interface 35) : 524288 Bit 20: -- User has control over Guest Network 4 (interface 36) :1048576 Bit 21: -- User has control over Guest Network 5 (interface 37) :2097152 Bit 22: -- User has control over Guest Network 6 (interface 38) :4194304 Bit 23: -- User has control over Guest Network 7 (interface 39) :8388608 This object value is stored in non-vol and set to 1 after factory reset.

saRgDot11ExtMbssUseNonvol.name: saRgDot11ExtMbssUseNonvol
saRgDot11ExtMbssUseNonvol.description: Allows to save additional BSS parameters to non-vol if set to true. Primary BSS parameters are ALWAYS stored in non-vol. This object value is stored in non-vol and set to false after factory reset.

saRgDot11ExtMbssAdminControl.name: saRgDot11ExtMbssAdminControl
saRgDot11ExtMbssAdminControl.description: Sets the number of admin controlled Wifi networks via web pages. 1: The admin has control over the primary wireless network only. No guest network page is displayed. 2: The admin has control over the primary wireless network and one guest network. No drop down menu (or only 1 item in the menu) for additional guest network configuration. 3: Same as above with 2 guest networks. 4: Same as above with 3 guest networks. 5: Same as above with 4 guest networks. 6: Same as above with 5 guest networks. 7: Same as above with 6 guest networks. 8: Same as above with 7 guest networks. Bit 16: -- Admin Has control over Primary Wireless Network : 65536 Bit 17: -- Admin Has control over Guest Network 1 (interface 33) : 131072 Bit 18: -- Admin Has control over Guest Network 2 (interface 34) : 262144 Bit 19: -- Admin Has control over Guest Network 3 (interface 35) : 524288 Bit 20: -- Admin Has control over Guest Network 4 (interface 36) :1048576 Bit 21: -- Admin Has control over Guest Network 5 (interface 37) :2097152 Bit 22: -- Admin Has control over Guest Network 6 (interface 38) :4194304 Bit 23: -- Admin Has control over Guest Network 7 (interface 39) :8388608 This object value is stored in non-vol and set to 1 after factory reset.

saRgDot11ExtActualChannel.name: saRgDot11ExtActualChannel
saRgDot11ExtActualChannel.description: Reports the current channel number that wireless is on. The value of 0 means wireless is disabled.

saRgDot11ApplySettings.name: saRgDot11ApplySettings
saRgDot11ApplySettings.description: If set to true(1), then all the settings (MIB values) from this MIB tree will be applied to run time configuration, modifying previous RG operation with the new settings. Before setting the value to true, MIBs modified in the MIB tree are stored in non-vol and will not modify RG operation until saRgDot11ApplySettings is set to true or CM resets. Note: this applies only to the MIB objects that are stored in non-vol. Always returns false(2) when read.

saRgIpMgmtLanTable.name: saRgIpMgmtLanTable
saRgIpMgmtLanTable.description: Networks on the LAN side. Primary BSS stored in non-vol.

saRgIpMgmtLanEntry.name: saRgIpMgmtLanEntry
saRgIpMgmtLanEntry.description: List of networks on the LAN side.

saRgIpMgmtLanMode.name: saRgIpMgmtLanMode
saRgIpMgmtLanMode.description: Defines the mode of operation for the device. Setting this object via SNMP for the primary BSS will cause the unit to reboot. Setting this object via SNMP for the secondary BSSs will not cause the unit to reboot. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol and is router after factory reset. The default value for other BSSs is router. This MIB supersedes saRgDeviceMode for the .32 interface. l2tpv2-client(3)is obsoleted and NOT supported. bridge(1): Sets individual interface to bridging mode (for IPv6 interfaces DHCPv6 is external) router(2): Sets individual interface to routing mode (for IPv6 interfaces DHCPv6 is internal) l2tpv2-client(3): <obsolete> mixed(4): For mixed mode. This setting is applicable only to .32 interface. This value is used on conjunction with saRgIpMgmtLanPortControlTable *Note: mixed(4) mode NOT Supported by DOCSIS 2.0 products. vlan (5): Enables the vlan control feature. See saRgVlanTable MIBs for VLAN configuration information.

saRgIpMgmtLanNetwork.name: saRgIpMgmtLanNetwork
saRgIpMgmtLanNetwork.description: The LAN-Trans network number. Default for primary BSS is 192.168.0.0 Default for other BSSs is 192.168.ifIndex.0

saRgIpMgmtLanNetworksAllow.name: saRgIpMgmtLanNetworksAllow
saRgIpMgmtLanNetworksAllow.description: Allows the user via the internal Web GUI (Lan Setup page to input an IPv4 public or private Local IP address other than a class C Private address (the default Network for the Primary BSS = 192.168.0.0/24, with the default Local Ip address = 192.168.0.1.) In all cases the mask must be 255.255.255.x since the RG is limited to supporting a maximum of 253 IP addresses. (See RFC1918 for a description of private IP addresses and specified ranges.) Available Mib settings: default(0): Only the third and fourth octets are editable in the Web GUI for the Local IP address (Ex. 192.168.x.x/24). anyPrivateClass(1): All 4 octets are editable in the Web GUI for Local IP address, but the network specified must be a Private class A, B or C network address. (Ex. A=10.x.x.x, B=172.16.x.x, C=192.168.x.x). anyClass(2): All 4 octets are editable in the Web GUI for Local IP address, and the network specified could be any public or private class A, B, or C address. If the MSO specifically sets a Local IP address in saRgIpMgmtLanNetwork to a value other than the default value (for example: 192.168.0.1) then these fields will be uneditable by the user (grayed out).

saRgIpMgmtLanSubnetMask.name: saRgIpMgmtLanSubnetMask
saRgIpMgmtLanSubnetMask.description: The device MUST provide the value of this MIB object in the Option 1 (Subnet Mask) of DHCP OFFER and ACK messages sent to a LAN IP Device.

saRgIpMgmtLanGateway.name: saRgIpMgmtLanGateway
saRgIpMgmtLanGateway.description: The type of this address is specified by saRgIpMgmtLanNetwokRouterType. The PS MUST provide the value of this MIB object in the Option 3 (Router IP address) of the DHCP OFFER and ACK messages sent to the LAN IP Device. Default for primary BSS is 192.168.0.1 Default for other BSSs is 192.168.ifIndex.1

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServer.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServer
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServer.description: The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol. The default value for other BSSs is: Enabled by default if interface is in router mode. Always disabled if interface is in bridge mode.

saRgIpMgmtLanNapt.name: saRgIpMgmtLanNapt
saRgIpMgmtLanNapt.description: The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol. The default value for other BSSs is: Enabled by default if interface is in router mode. Always disabled if interface is in bridge mode.

saRgIpMgmtLanTypeOfService.name: saRgIpMgmtLanTypeOfService
saRgIpMgmtLanTypeOfService.description: Definition of the TOS bits for the Network. This object does not apply to primary BSS.

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcp125Option.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcp125Option
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcp125Option.description: This option controls if the RG adds a Cisco specific suboption (number 17) to DHCP DISCOVER and REQUEST from the clients that are bridged on the BSS: 0: do not add the option 1: add suboption 17 to Cisco specific enterprise-id (9) within DHCP option 125. The content is the SSID name.

saRgIpMgmtLanUpnp.name: saRgIpMgmtLanUpnp
saRgIpMgmtLanUpnp.description: Enable/Disable the UPnP agent. The value is stored in non-vol and is disabled after factory default for the primary SSID. The UPnP agents for additional networks are enabled by default.

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpOption43.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpOption43
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpOption43.description: If option 60 is set from the CPE then return this value in option 43 of the DHCP Reply. If this value is null then do not reply with option 43 (default is null) This MIB will apply to the Primary SSID (intface .32) only

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerTable.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerTable
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerTable.description: Networks on the LAN side. Stored in non-vol. .10-.128 for primary BSS after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerEntry.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerEntry
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerEntry.description: List of networks on the LAN side.

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolStart.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolStart
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolStart.description: The start of range LAN Trans IP Addresses. The type of this address is specified by saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolStartType. Default value depends on IP network and subnet.

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolEnd.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolEnd
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolEnd.description: The end of range for LAN-Trans IP Addresses. The type of this address is specified by saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerPoolEndType. Default value depends on IP network and subnet.

saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerLeaseTime.name: saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerLeaseTime
saRgIpMgmtLanDhcpServerLeaseTime.description: The PS MUST provide the value of this MIB object in the Option 51 (IP Address lease time) of the DHCP OFFER and ACK messages sent to the LAN IP Device.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrTable.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrTable
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrTable.description: IP addresses of devices served by DHCP servers.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrEntry.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrEntry
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrEntry.description: List of general parameters pertaining to LAN-Trans IP address reservations and leases.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrIndex.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrIndex
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrIndex.description: The index of the the LAN IP Device in the LAN-Trans Realm.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrPhysAddr.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrPhysAddr
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrPhysAddr.description: The client's (i.e., LAN IP Device's) hardware address as indicated in the chaddr field of its DHCP REQUEST message.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrLeaseCreateTime.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrLeaseCreateTime
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrLeaseCreateTime.description: This is the date and time when the LAN IP lease was created (if it has not yet been renewed) or last renewed.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrLeaseExpireTime.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrLeaseExpireTime
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrLeaseExpireTime.description: This is the date and time when the LAN IP address lease expired or will expire.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrHostName.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrHostName
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrHostName.description: This is the Host Name of the LAN IP address, based on DCHP option 12.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrClientId.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrClientId
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrClientId.description: This is the Client Class Identifier, based on DHCP option 60.

saRgIpMgmtLanAddrInterface.name: saRgIpMgmtLanAddrInterface
saRgIpMgmtLanAddrInterface.description: This will show the associated interface (LAN, WiFi or MoCA) of the connected CPE.

saRgIpMgmtDnsServerTable.name: saRgIpMgmtDnsServerTable
saRgIpMgmtDnsServerTable.description: This table contains the IP addresses of cable network and Internet DNS servers, in the order of preference in which the PS's CNP will query them, when it cannot resolve a DNS query using local information. Entries in this table are updated with the information contained in DHCP Option 6, received during both the WAN-Man and WAN-Data IP acquisition processes. Stored in non-vol and 0.0.0.0 for all servers after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtDnsServerEntry.name: saRgIpMgmtDnsServerEntry
saRgIpMgmtDnsServerEntry.description: List of cable network and Internet DNS servers.

saRgIpMgmtDnsServerIp.name: saRgIpMgmtDnsServerIp
saRgIpMgmtDnsServerIp.description: This parameter indicates the IP address of a WAN DNS server.

saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpTable.name: saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpTable
saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpTable.description: Fixed IP address assignments for DHCP server. Table does not return any row if DHCP disabled. The value for primary BSS is stored in non-vol.

saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpEntry.name: saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpEntry
saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpEntry.description: List of general parameters pertaining to LAN-Trans IP address reservations and leases.

saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpIndex.name: saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpIndex
saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpIndex.description: The index of the the LAN IP Device in the LAN-Trans Realm.

saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpRowStatus.name: saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpRowStatus
saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpRowStatus.description: The row status. A row can be destroyed.

saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpPhysAddr.name: saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpPhysAddr
saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpPhysAddr.description: The client's (i.e., LAN IP Device's) hardware address as indicated in the chaddr field of its DHCP REQUEST message.

saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpHostName.name: saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpHostName
saRgIpMgmtDhcpFixedIpHostName.description: This is the Host Name of the LAN IP address, based on DCHP option 12.

saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteTable.name: saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteTable
saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteTable.description: Static route entries in the routing table. This table is saved in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteEntry.name: saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteEntry
saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteEntry.description: List of static route entries in the routing table.

saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteIndex.name: saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteIndex
saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteIndex.description: The index of the the table.

saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteGateway.name: saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteGateway
saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteGateway.description: Gateway to the network defined in saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteNetwork and saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteSubnetMask.

saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteRipAdvertise.name: saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteRipAdvertise
saRgIpMgmtStaticRouteRipAdvertise.description: If set to true(1), then static route entry will be advertised in RIP.

saRgIpMgmtWanMode.name: saRgIpMgmtWanMode
saRgIpMgmtWanMode.description: When dualIp(3) is selected, the second IP stack is used for user operations. Stored in non-vol, dhcp(1) after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtWanMtu.name: saRgIpMgmtWanMtu
saRgIpMgmtWanMtu.description: MTU size for the IP layer. Valid range is 256 to 1500. 0 is the default which is 1500. Stored in non-vol, 0 after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtWanTtl.name: saRgIpMgmtWanTtl
saRgIpMgmtWanTtl.description: TTL for the IP packets forwarded to WAN. 0 means no change to the original TTL (after being decreased by 1). Stored in non-vol, 0 after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtWanStaticNetwork.name: saRgIpMgmtWanStaticNetwork
saRgIpMgmtWanStaticNetwork.description: Stored in non-vol, 0.0.0.0 after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtWanStaticSubnetMask.name: saRgIpMgmtWanStaticSubnetMask
saRgIpMgmtWanStaticSubnetMask.description: Stored in non-vol, 0.0.0.0 after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtWanStaticGateway.name: saRgIpMgmtWanStaticGateway
saRgIpMgmtWanStaticGateway.description: Stored in non-vol, 0.0.0.0 after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtWanDualIpAddr.name: saRgIpMgmtWanDualIpAddr
saRgIpMgmtWanDualIpAddr.description: IP address for the second IP stack. If not specified and saRgIpMgmtWanMode is set to dualIp(3), DHCP is used to acquire the IP address. Note: this object can only be set from config file.

saRgIpMgmtWanDualIpRipAdvertised.name: saRgIpMgmtWanDualIpRipAdvertised
saRgIpMgmtWanDualIpRipAdvertised.description: Specifies if the IP address is to be advertised in RIP, if RIP is enabled. Note: this object can only be set from config file.

saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetTable.name: saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetTable
saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetTable.description: Additional IP addresses for primary LAN interface. If RIP is enabled, all subnets are advertised. All objects are stored in non-vol. The table is empty after factory reset.

saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetEntry.name: saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetEntry
saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetEntry.description: List of networks on the LAN side.

saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetIndex.name: saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetIndex
saRgIpMgmtLanExtraSubnetIndex.description: Indicates the instance of this table row.

saRgIpMgmtLanPortControlTable.name: saRgIpMgmtLanPortControlTable
saRgIpMgmtLanPortControlTable.description: Table to control the mode for each LAN PORT. LAN PORTs are numbered 1-4 and are mapped to physical port location. Each port can either be in router or in bridge mode.

saRgIpMgmtLanPortControlIndex.name: saRgIpMgmtLanPortControlIndex
saRgIpMgmtLanPortControlIndex.description: The index for each LAN port

saRgIpMgmtLanPortMode.name: saRgIpMgmtLanPortMode
saRgIpMgmtLanPortMode.description: Each physical LAN port can either be controlled as bridge or router. The saRgIpMgmtLanPortMode MIB only works when SaRgIpMgmtLanMode.32=4(Mixed). Setting this MIB through SNMP will take effect only after saRgIpMgmtApplySettings.0 set to true and this setting will reboot to take effect

saRgIpMgmtApplySettings.name: saRgIpMgmtApplySettings
saRgIpMgmtApplySettings.description: If set to true(1), then all the settings (MIB values) from this MIB tree will be applied to run time configuration, modifying previous RG operation with the new settings. Before setting the value to true, MIBs modified in the MIB tree are stored in non-vol and will not modify RG operation until saRgIpMgmtApplySettings is set to true or CM resets. Note: this applies only to the MIB objects that are stored in non-vol. Always returns false(2) when read.

saRgFirewallReportEventTable.name: saRgFirewallReportEventTable
saRgFirewallReportEventTable.description: This table is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallReportMgmtClearLog.name: saRgFirewallReportMgmtClearLog
saRgFirewallReportMgmtClearLog.description: Note: this object does not need saRgFirewallApplySettings to take effect.

saRgFirewallReportEmailLogNow.name: saRgFirewallReportEmailLogNow
saRgFirewallReportEmailLogNow.description: Triggers sending currect logs via email. Always returns false. Note: this objects does not need saRgFirewallApplySettings to send the logs.

saRgFirewallReportEmailEnable.name: saRgFirewallReportEmailEnable
saRgFirewallReportEmailEnable.description: Enables sending logs via email. Email is sent when an event happens.

saRgFirewallReportEmailAddress.name: saRgFirewallReportEmailAddress
saRgFirewallReportEmailAddress.description: This is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallReportEmailSmtpServer.name: saRgFirewallReportEmailSmtpServer
saRgFirewallReportEmailSmtpServer.description: IP address or FQDN. Stored in non-vol. Empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallReportEmailUsername.name: saRgFirewallReportEmailUsername
saRgFirewallReportEmailUsername.description: This is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallReportEmailPassword.name: saRgFirewallReportEmailPassword
saRgFirewallReportEmailPassword.description: This is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallIpFilterTable.name: saRgFirewallIpFilterTable
saRgFirewallIpFilterTable.description: This table is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallIpFilterRowStatus.name: saRgFirewallIpFilterRowStatus
saRgFirewallIpFilterRowStatus.description: The row status. A row can be destroyed. If the row is not used, set to notInService.

saRgFirewallPortFilterTable.name: saRgFirewallPortFilterTable
saRgFirewallPortFilterTable.description: This table is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallPortFilterRowStatus.name: saRgFirewallPortFilterRowStatus
saRgFirewallPortFilterRowStatus.description: The row status. A row can be destroyed. If the row is not used, set to notInService.

saRgFirewallMacFilterTable.name: saRgFirewallMacFilterTable
saRgFirewallMacFilterTable.description: A table of clients MAC addresses that are denied from accessing Internet.

saRgFirewallMacFilterEntry.name: saRgFirewallMacFilterEntry
saRgFirewallMacFilterEntry.description: A row in the table that specifies a single station MAC address.

saRgFirewallMacFilterRowStatus.name: saRgFirewallMacFilterRowStatus
saRgFirewallMacFilterRowStatus.description: The row status. A row can be destroyed. If the row is not used, set to notInService.

saRgFirewallMacFilterAddress.name: saRgFirewallMacFilterAddress
saRgFirewallMacFilterAddress.description: A MAC address of a station that cannot access Internet.

saRgFirewallMacFilterEnable.name: saRgFirewallMacFilterEnable
saRgFirewallMacFilterEnable.description: True = Enable the Mac address filtering feature. False = disable. this Value is written to non-vol and set to false after a factory reset.

saRgFirewallMacFilterMode.name: saRgFirewallMacFilterMode
saRgFirewallMacFilterMode.description: block(0)- Macs listed in the saRgFirewallMacFilterEntryTable will be blocked. permit(1)- Macs listed in the saRgFirewallMacFilterEntryTable will be permitted. This value is written to non-vol and is set to block(0) after a factory reset.

saRgFirewallPortFwdTable.name: saRgFirewallPortFwdTable
saRgFirewallPortFwdTable.description: This table is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallPortFwdRowStatus.name: saRgFirewallPortFwdRowStatus
saRgFirewallPortFwdRowStatus.description: The row status. A row can be destroyed. If the row is not used, set to notInService.

saRgFirewallPortFwdToAddress.name: saRgFirewallPortFwdToAddress
saRgFirewallPortFwdToAddress.description: Valid address must be entered for a row to be created.

saRgFirewallPortFwdPortStart.name: saRgFirewallPortFwdPortStart
saRgFirewallPortFwdPortStart.description: Valid port must be entered for a row to be created.

saRgFirewallPortFwdPortEnd.name: saRgFirewallPortFwdPortEnd
saRgFirewallPortFwdPortEnd.description: Valid port must be entered for a row to be created.

saRgFirewallPortFwdExternalPortStart.name: saRgFirewallPortFwdExternalPortStart
saRgFirewallPortFwdExternalPortStart.description: Valid port must be entered for a row to be created. This is the outside-facing start port for the portforward.

saRgFirewallPortFwdExternalPortEnd.name: saRgFirewallPortFwdExternalPortEnd
saRgFirewallPortFwdExternalPortEnd.description: Valid port must be entered for a row to be created. This is the outside-facing end port for the portforward.

saRgFirewallPortTrigTable.name: saRgFirewallPortTrigTable
saRgFirewallPortTrigTable.description: This table is stored in non-vol and is empty after factory reset.

saRgFirewallPortTrigRowStatus.name: saRgFirewallPortTrigRowStatus
saRgFirewallPortTrigRowStatus.description: The row status. A row can be destroyed. If the row is not used, set to notInService.

saRgFirewallApplySettings.name: saRgFirewallApplySettings
saRgFirewallApplySettings.description: If set to true(1), then all the settings (MIB values) from this MIB tree will be applied to run time configuration, modifying previous RG operation with the new settings. Before setting the value to true, MIBs modified in the MIB tree are stored in non-vol and will not modify RG operation until saRgFirewallApplySettings is set to true or CM resets. Note: this applies only to the MIB objects that are stored in non-vol. Always returns false(2) when read.

saRgDsliteOption.name: saRgDsliteOption
saRgDsliteOption.description: This MIB will toggle whether DHCPv6 option 64 is requested in the solicit. The option should only be requested if DS Lite is enabled.

saRgDsliteAftrName.name: saRgDsliteAftrName
saRgDsliteAftrName.description: This MIB will read/write the remote IPv6 FQDN of the AFTR router in the DS Lite tunnel configuration. This should only have an effect if eRouter is in IPv6 only mode and DS Lite is enabled.

saRgDsliteAftrAddress.name: saRgDsliteAftrAddress
saRgDsliteAftrAddress.description: This MIB will set the remote IPv6 address of the AFTR router manually in the DS Lite tunnel configuration. This should only have an effect if eRouter is in IPv6 only mode and DS Lite is enabled.

saRgDsliteTcpMssClamping.name: saRgDsliteTcpMssClamping
saRgDsliteTcpMssClamping.description: Specifies whether TCP MSS clamping is enabled on the interface. 0 disables clamping, 1 clamps the MSS depending on the interface MTU. A value > 1 will be used as clamping size. This MIB takes effect immediately and does not require saRgDsliteApplySettings.

saRgDsliteApplySettings.name: saRgDsliteApplySettings
saRgDsliteApplySettings.description: If set to true(1), then all the settings (MIB values) from this MIB tree will be applied to the runtime configuration, This will resolve the AFTR domain name to the AFTR IPv6 address, and initialize the DSlite tunnel. This will initialize using the AFTR address if both the address and FQDN are defined. This should only activate the tunnel if eRouter is in IPv6 only mode and DS Lite is enabled. Always returns false(2) when read.
